form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: DECISION ON APPLICATION FOR STATUS AS PERMANENT RESIDENT, I-291

full_text: U.S. Department of Justice Immigration and Naturalization Service 300 North Los Angeles Street DECISION ON APPLICATION FOR Los Angeles, CA 90012 STATUS AS PERMANENT RESIDENT Refer To This File No. Francisca Hortencia Toledo A70 023 120 4818 Henton Avenue Covina, CA 91724 Date: June 131991 (HAND DELIVERED) Upon consideration, it is ordered that your application for status as a permanent resident be denied for the following reasons: SEE ATTACHMENT You are granted to July 12/491 to effect your departure from the United States voluntarily, without the institution of proceedings to enforce your departure. You must notify this office before that date on the enclosed card (Form 1-438) of the arrangements you have made to depart from the United States. At the time of your departure from the United States, do not fail to surrender Form I-94, Arrival-Departure Record, in accordance with the instructions on that form. If you fail to depart from the United States by the date specified, proceedings will be instituted to enforce your departure. You may renew your application for status as a permanent resident during such proceedings. Sincerely yours, District Director I-438 J-94 Lam Enclosure(s) Passport Form 1-291 (Rev. 11-1-83) Y
